The paper deals with the problem of coordination in a network, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of common randomness and communication over a network suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper's focus on developing insight into the interplay between communication and coordination suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
